com.ibm.team.process.common

Interface IBehaviorConfiguration


  • public interface IBehaviorConfiguration
    A behavior configuration represents the behavior specified in the process specification/customization for a specific operation. A configuration is given as a set of IProcessConfigurationElement.
    Since:
    0.6

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      IProcessConfigurationElement[] getElements()
      Returns the process configuration elements specified in this configuration.
      java.lang.String getId()
      Returns the unique id of the operation for which this configuration has been specified.
      IOperationConfigurationInfo getOperationConfigurationInfo()
      Returns the configuration info which contains information about how this configuration was retrieved by the process framework.
